{{Confused|Zazas}} {{Cleanup|date=May 2009}} {{unsourced|date=October 2016}}
The '''Zazi''' ({{lang-ps|ځاځی; plur. ځاځي}}), also spelled '''Zazai''', or '''Jaji''', is a [[Karlani]] [[Pashtun people|Pashtun]] tribe. They are found in [[Paktia province|Paktia]] and [[Khost province|Khost]] provinces in the [[Loya Paktia]] region of southeastern [[Afghanistan]], as well as [[Kurram Valley]] of Pakistan, but also have an effective presence in [[Kabul]], [[Logar Province|Logar]], [[Ghazni]], [[Nangharhar]], [[Kunduz]], and [[Baghlan]] in Afghanistan.{{citation needed|date=October 2017}}
==Ethnicity and geography== The Zazi are similar to the [[Wardak(Pashtun tribe)|Wardak]] and [[Turi (Pashtun tribe)|Turi]], except that the Zazi are [[Sunni]] Muslims. The tribe is inhabited in four major geographic locations in Afghanistan and Pakistan:
*'''Aryob Zazi''': in Paktia province *'''Ahmad Khel ''': in Paktia province *'''Dand Pathan''': in Paktia province *'''Kabul''': in Kabul province *'''Maidan Zazi''': district in Khost province *'''Kwarma (Kurram) Zazi''': [[Kurram Agency]] in the Federally Administered Tribal Areas
==Notable Zazi== *[[Abdullah Jan Jaji]] was founder of M/s Abdullah Jan Jaji Co,.Ltd & Afghan Shaheen industry from zazi. *[[Abdul Rahman Jaji]] s/o late Abdullah Jan Jaji a famous Afghan business from zazi. *[[Qutbuddin Hilal]], [[Deputy Prime Minister]] of [[Afghanistan]] during the period of Mujahideen ([[Gulbuddin Hekmatyar]]) and member of [[Hezbi Islami]] from [[Zazi_Maidan_District|Zazi Maidan]] district. *[[Nabi Misdaq]], founder of [[BBC]] Pashto service. *[[Najibullah Zazi]] (born 1985), Afghan-born man imprisoned in the USA for terrorist offenses; father is [[Mohammed Wali Zazi]]. *[[Haji Mohammad Omar Khan Mumtaz Zazai]],Well-know Afghan and International Businessman owner of "The Afghan Mumtaz Group Of Companies"+Tribal Chief of Ali-Khel Zazai. *[[Ahmad Mumtaz Khan Zazai]],The son of Mohammad Omar Khan Mumtaz Zazai and after his father passed away in 2006 became the Tribal Chief of Ali-Khel Zazai and the CEO of Afghan Mumtaz Group Of Companies.
